President Obama has named fifteen recipients of the Presidential Medal of Freedom, the highest civilian honor in the United States. The recipients include former President George H. W. Bush, Chancellor Angela Merkel of Germany, Congressman John Lewis, environmentalist John H. Adams, author Maya Angelou, investor Warren Buffett, artist Jasper Johns, Holocaust survivor Gerda Weissmann Klein, optometrist Dr. Tom Little (posthumously), cellist Yo-Yo Ma, civil rights activist Sylvia Mendez, baseball player Stan Musial, basketball player Bill Russell, founder of VSA Jean Kennedy Smith, and labor leader John J. Sweeney. The awards will be presented at a White House ceremony early next year.